\begin_layout Standard
With the mathematical underpinnings set, Part 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "part:2"

\end_inset

 will focus on the theoretical aspects of the thesis.
 The general problem of conducting inference on data in the form of distribution
s is introduced and formalized in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "chap:EM"

\end_inset

.
 A procedure for conducting inference is developed and an interpretation
 of such a procedure as being a limited case of MLE on a misspecified model
 is also given.
 An expectation-maximization algorithm is developed to address the problem
 of intractable transition densities for most diffusion processes.
 However, the need to exactly sample generalized diffusion bridges becomes
 apparent if we wish to be able to carry out such an EM algorithm under
 Monte Carlo framework.
 As such, in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "chap:4"

\end_inset

, a simulation strategy for approximate and exact generalized diffusion
 bridges of this sort is given, as well as the marginal density of such
 a bridge.
